        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thank you @CaoKha  for the input. I pushed some changes based on `git grep`. But with some differences to your solution: \r\n\r\n1. I match both single and double quoted imports (`@import 'tailwindcss'` and `@import \"tailwindcss\"`) via a `targets` list, which also makes it easy to add new patterns later. This is something that I already did in a previous (merged) commit. But we cannot use the lua pattern here for the `git grep`, so I needed to update it. \r\n 2. I added `--untracked` to git grep so newly created but not yet staged CSS files are also found.\r\n 3. If git grep runs successfully but finds nothing (exit code ≤ 1), I return `nil` immediately instead of falling back to the filesystem scan. No match means it's simply not a tailwind project I would say\r\n 4. I cast `math.huge` with `--[[@as integer]]` to fix a LuaLS type mismatch on the depth parameter.\r\n\r\nI appreciate some check, since I am not a regular contributor or lua expert. ",
